parameters:
I met her directly by chance when I was passing by near
the university's pool.

The university's lecture hall was made up of a pool and
gym in the basement, a large lecture hall on the first
floor with a basketball court, and a small lecture hall
on the second floor with a badminton court.

I heard somewhere that the gym was free, so I thought
I'd give exercise a try and went to the lecture hall
for the first time.

When I was muttering to myself in my mind, Why is the
staircase only in this corner?

I could faintly hear the sound of water and see a pool
through the window glass of the spiral staircase.

Since the lecture time had already passed, I thought most
people had already gone home, but...

After I saw her swimming there, I was captivated and sneaked
into the pool area.
There was no one else at the pool except for her.

I couldn't help but gaze at her beautiful and powerful
swimming style.

The water droplets scattered on the water's surface,
creating a blurred white light, as she continued her
race.
The boy meets the girl.

I thought about how if I were the protagonist of the
story, it would have started with an introduction like
this.

It was a great shock that brought about a tremendous
change in my ordinary life up until now.
akane_sui (2)
Akane
......Huh? Is someone there...?
Hikaru
I'm in trouble.
She's probably going to think of me as a complete pervert.
Akane
Hmm, are you a fan? Or maybe not?
Akane

Hey, if you've been watching me this whole time, could you
hold the timer for me?
Akane

Today, I'm feeling really good, so I wanted to time myself,
but the coach's sister stepped out for a moment.
Hikaru
U-um, yeah. Can I use the timer on my phone?
Akane
Sure~. Well then, I'll leave it to you.
Akane
I'm going to do two laps.

They don't seem to mind being watched by others at all, but
they seem to have mistaken me for a fan.

Maybe there were quite a few people who came here to see
her, like fans or something.
So, her name is... I think...

...Akane, I think... I feel like I've heard that name somewhere
before.
akane_sui (1)
Akane
Phew... How many seconds!?
Hikaru
Um, let's see... 2 seconds... no, 2 minutes and 1 second.
akane_sui (5)
Akane
Ehhh... Even though I thought I was feeling good today...
Akane
It hasn't decreased at all...

They looked visibly down, so I feel a little sorry for
them.

I formed a hypothesis, wondering if the reason they were
shaking every time they took a rough breath was not due
to the resistance of the water they had received.

But rather if the reason the time doesn't decrease is due
to the non-streamlined part of her body, I wonder.

If I were to say that, they would definitely report it to
the police.
Well, in the end, I couldn't go to the gym that day.
